The European Council on Tolerance and Reconciliation (also ECTR) is a non-governmental organization that was established in Paris, France on October 7, 2008 to monitor tolerance in Europe. The Chairman of the Council is former British Prime Minister Tony Blair (until 2013 - former President of Poland Aleksander Kwa≈õniewski), and the President of the Council is Viatcheslav Moshe Kantor.
